data.text:
"Hippo Bird" was composed by Arthur Harold Wilkinson. The main instruments played in the piece include a bassoon, flute, pizzicato strings, and a harp.

Usage[]

232a. "Mustard O' Mine" - SpongeBob, Patrick, and Squidward outside the mustard mine.

234b. "ChefBob" - SpongeBob makes a paper bag puppet called ChefBob.

248b. "Squid's on a Bus" - "You big clod! I could do your job better than you ever could!"

249a. "Sandy's Nutty Nieces" - SpongeBob turns on the TV.

253a. "Jolly Lodgers" - Hotel manager comes back to the reception and rewards SpongeBob and Patrick.

260b. "Pat Hearts Squid" - "Be quiet down there or I'm calling the cops!"

266. "Escape from Beneath Glove World" - SpongeBob and Patrick see the little kid wearing Hieronymus Glove robot's body and runs away.

269b. "Squidward's Sick Daze" - "You are in no conditions to be alone. That's why I brought you some help."

274a. "The Big Bad Bubble Bass" - "Hey, what part of 'not interested' don't you understand?"

276b. "Patrick the Mailman" - SpongeBob and Patrick go to Old Man Walker's house.

284a. "The Flower Plot" - Petunia about to make a delivery.

294b. "Buff for Puff" - Mr. Krabs bench pressing bags of money.

296b. "Squidiot Box" - Squidward finds a staircase.

298a. "Momageddon" - SpongeBob invited Mr. Krabs and Squidward's moms.
